The paper focuses on analyzing citation behavior in the field of natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to develop a classifier, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also analyzes how citations are followed by readers, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
